to the editor re laid off workers swelling the cost of disability pay front page sept 2 the government could improve the situation of low skilled american workers by reducing the influx of low skilled foreign workers who are often willing to work long hours in bad conditions for wages below what americans will accept according to a 1997 national academy of sciences study competition with low skilled immigrants was responsible for nearly half of the decline in the wages of high school dropouts from 1980 to 1995 to continue admitting large numbers of low skilled workers into the country now when the economy is in trouble is a betrayal of the american worker john brock staten island sept 2 2002

